# UI and Styling Guidelines

## NuxtUI Components
- Prefer NuxtUI 4 components over custom implementations
- Use built-in components: `UButton`, `UCard`, `UInput`, `UModal`, etc.
- Leverage NuxtUI's theming and customization options
- Follow NuxtUI's component API and props

## Tailwind CSS
- Use Tailwind CSS v4 for styling
- Implement mobile-first responsive design
- Use utility classes for custom styling
- Follow Tailwind's design system principles

## Responsive Design
- Use mobile-first approach with Tailwind breakpoints
- Implement proper responsive layouts
- Test on multiple screen sizes
- Use Tailwind's responsive utilities

## Accessibility
- Ensure components are accessible by default
- Use proper ARIA attributes
- Implement keyboard navigation
- Test with screen readers
- Follow WCAG guidelines

## Performance
- Optimize images: use WebP format, include size data
- Implement lazy loading for images and components
- Use Nuxt's built-in image optimization
- Minimize CSS bundle size

## Custom Styling
- Use CSS custom properties for theming
- Implement consistent design tokens
- Use Tailwind's @apply directive sparingly
- Keep custom CSS minimal and focused
